I talked to Mr. Ma and it went well.

573
00:37:42.538 --> 00:37:43.808
I will sleep first.

574
00:37:44.447 --> 00:37:45.777
that there's no way to reach your heart.

575
00:37:47.308 --> 00:37:51.748
What if there's just no way to reach your heart...

576
00:37:53.788 --> 00:37:55.318
at all?

577
00:37:56.257 --> 00:37:58.088
That's what I'm afraid of.

578
00:37:59.128 --> 00:38:00.628
I received the address.

579
00:38:00.827 --> 00:38:03.228
I'll go help your family make kimchi.

580
00:38:03.858 --> 00:38:05.568
But for now,

581
00:38:07.297 --> 00:38:08.938
I can't do anything about it.

582
00:38:11.338 --> 00:38:13.808
I don't know the way to reach his heart.

583
00:38:15.407 --> 00:38:17.748
But he does know where to go make kimchi.

584
00:38:18.447 --> 00:38:19.677
That's him,

585
00:38:27.918 --> 00:38:30.117
and I like him.

586
00:38:31.887 --> 00:38:33.887
For now,

587
00:38:37.527 --> 00:38:38.797
that is enough.

588
00:38:41.998 --> 00:38:43.268
Really?

589
00:38:43.367 --> 00:38:47.108
Just some bottles of makgeolli won't be enough while making kimchi.

590
00:38:47.208 --> 00:38:50.338
Just get a lot that's enough to fill a whole bucket.

591
00:38:51.447 --> 00:38:53.277
Okay.

592
00:38:54.077 --> 00:38:56.777
Ji Seok and our daughter-in-law will be here soon.

593
00:38:57.518 --> 00:38:59.717
It's not even a national event.

594
00:38:59.717 --> 00:39:02.257
Why did you tell her to come here? She's pregnant.

595
00:39:02.257 --> 00:39:04.257
Where's Ji Ho? When is she going to be here?

596
00:39:04.927 --> 00:39:07.387
Ji Ho doesn't have time for that.

597
00:39:07.527 --> 00:39:09.558
She is busy making her living in Seoul.

598
00:39:09.558 --> 00:39:12.068
She's doing nothing at home. What's making her busy?

599
00:39:12.068 --> 00:39:15.938
She's married now. She should learn how to make kimchi.

600
00:39:16.038 --> 00:39:18.068
Goodness.

601
00:39:23.838 --> 00:39:25.308
Hey, Ji Ho. What's going on?

602
00:39:26.808 --> 00:39:29.248
What? Who's coming here?

603
00:39:29.347 --> 00:39:31.117
Yes, later to help you.

604
00:39:31.288 --> 00:39:32.947
What about your work?

605
00:39:32.947 --> 00:39:34.987
I can't go,

606
00:39:35.288 --> 00:39:37.288
but someone else will go in place of me.

607
00:39:37.588 --> 00:39:38.927
Who's coming?

608
00:39:55.808 --> 00:39:58.007
Hey! It's cold. Close the window.

609
00:40:22.668 --> 00:40:24.407
You've deviated from the original course.

610
00:40:25.768 --> 00:40:28.137
- What? - This is not the right direction.

611
00:40:29.938 --> 00:40:31.708
I'm searching for the right direction.

612
00:40:37.688 --> 00:40:39.688
You're making so much.

613
00:40:39.788 --> 00:40:41.217
How could you buy 100 heads of cabbage...

614
00:40:41.217 --> 00:40:42.288
when we don't have enough people to work on?

615
00:40:42.487 --> 00:40:44.827
Don't worry about it.

616
00:40:45.628 --> 00:40:48.728
We'll be done before your husbands come home.

617
00:40:50.728 --> 00:40:53.097
By the way, is Ji Ho not coming?

618
00:40:53.527 --> 00:40:54.768
- Ji Ho? - Yes.

619
00:40:55.438 --> 00:40:56.498
Oh, right.

620
00:40:56.998 --> 00:40:59.168
She told me someone else is coming instead of her.

621
00:40:59.467 --> 00:41:00.507
Who?

622
00:41:02.077 --> 00:41:04.038
- Excuse me. - I don't know.

623
00:41:04.108 --> 00:41:05.677
She told me to wait and see.

624
00:41:08.818 --> 00:41:09.847
Excuse me.

625
00:41:11.588 --> 00:41:12.688
Hello.

626
00:41:17.217 --> 00:41:18.558
Hey, Se Hee.

627
00:41:19.458 --> 00:41:21.827
What are you doing here?

628
00:41:22.027 --> 00:41:23.697
- Well... - He's Ji Ho's husband?

629
00:41:23.827 --> 00:41:25.628
- You're good-looking. - He is.

630
00:41:25.628 --> 00:41:28.137
- He's good-looking - He really is.

631
00:41:28.137 --> 00:41:30.168
- You're insane. - What?

632
00:41:30.168 --> 00:41:32.568
- Goodness. - Stop it.

633
00:41:33.768 --> 00:41:35.808
The whole neighborhood looks better with him in it.

634
00:41:37.708 --> 00:41:41.347
I'm here to help you with making kimchi.

635
00:41:43.478 --> 00:41:45.947
So you're the one Ji Ho said...

636
00:41:45.947 --> 00:41:48.188
- That's right. It's me. - Who's here?

637
00:41:48.688 --> 00:41:50.117
Hey, my son-in-law!

638
00:41:53.427 --> 00:41:55.858
What's going on? What are you doing here?

639
00:41:55.927 --> 00:41:58.728
I'm here to help with making kimchi.

640
00:41:59.197 --> 00:42:00.367
Kimchi?

641
00:42:01.268 --> 00:42:02.438
Yes.

642
00:42:02.938 --> 00:42:04.668
Come on in. Welcome.

643
00:42:04.668 --> 00:42:07.068
Bring us something to drink.

644
00:42:08.108 --> 00:42:09.438
Come on in.

645
00:42:09.608 --> 00:42:12.608
We can have bossam after they make kimchi for us.

646
00:42:12.808 --> 00:42:14.378
- Take a seat. - No, that's not right.

647
00:42:14.918 --> 00:42:18.148
I'm not here to have bossam but to help with making kimchi.

648
00:42:19.018 --> 00:42:20.958
I must help her make kimchi.

649
00:42:21.088 --> 00:42:22.188
What?

650
00:42:25.288 --> 00:42:26.987
Actually,

651
00:42:27.527 --> 00:42:30.027
Ji Ho helped with the ancestral rites...

652
00:42:30.297 --> 00:42:31.768
in my parents' place.

653
00:42:31.827 --> 00:42:34.197
That's why I agreed with her to share my labor...

654
00:42:34.297 --> 00:42:36.297
and time equivalent of how she spent hers in my parents'.

655
00:42:36.367 --> 00:42:38.068
What are you talking about?

656
00:42:38.068 --> 00:42:40.768
It's only natural for a daughter-in-law to do that.

657
00:42:41.808 --> 00:42:44.108
Is that right? She helped in your parents' place?

658
00:42:44.248 --> 00:42:45.308
Yes, she did.

659
00:42:46.208 --> 00:42:48.878
Stop talking nonsense, and sit down here.

660
00:42:49.018 --> 00:42:50.547
Let's have a drink.

661
00:42:50.547 --> 00:42:53.387
- I can't... - You'll have to get changed.

662
00:42:54.858 --> 00:42:58.157
You'll need something else to wear. Do you want mine?

663
00:42:59.288 --> 00:43:02.427
- Sure. I'd appreciate that. - Okay.

664
00:43:22.677 --> 00:43:24.018
I've arrived at your parents' place.

665
00:43:24.447 --> 00:43:27.918
We're making kimchi now.

666
00:43:29.058 --> 00:43:30.117
Is there something wrong?

667
00:43:30.318 --> 00:43:32.327
What? No, it's nothing.

668
00:43:34.827 --> 00:43:36.197
Hey, Soo Ji is here.

669
00:43:41.768 --> 00:43:44.838
She's pretty as usual. She's totally my type.

670
00:43:50.407 --> 00:43:51.547
What?

671
00:43:52.478 --> 00:43:53.608
Nothing.

672
00:43:54.878 --> 00:43:57.818
Your type...

673
00:43:58.347 --> 00:43:59.748
changes so fast.

674
00:44:00.958 --> 00:44:03.887
You used to tell me how pretty I am.

675
00:44:05.157 --> 00:44:07.387
I just thought you were a little cute.

676
00:44:07.728 --> 00:44:09.197
You're actually not my type.

677
00:44:19.338 --> 00:44:22.177
What? He went to make kimchi in Namhae?

678
00:44:23.308 --> 00:44:24.347
Yes.

679
00:44:25.878 --> 00:44:28.677
He's as amazing as you are.

680
00:44:29.447 --> 00:44:32.288
No wonder you two signed such a contract.

681
00:44:33.518 --> 00:44:36.518
What if he falls sick and can't make it back to Seoul?

682
00:44:37.018 --> 00:44:38.858
I'm sure your mom bought about 100 heads of cabbage.

683
00:44:40.387 --> 00:44:42.927
I don't think they'll make him help.

684
00:44:43.498 --> 00:44:45.827
He'll probably have some bossam and come back.

685
00:44:46.568 --> 00:44:49.338
I knew it already that they won't make him help.

686
00:45:18.128 --> 00:45:19.998
Put that in here.

687
00:45:19.998 --> 00:45:21.768
Where did the garlic go?

688
00:45:23.398 --> 00:45:25.068
How come you're so weak?

689
00:45:25.068 --> 00:45:26.768
Pull it!

690
00:45:27.907 --> 00:45:29.577
My goodness.

691
00:45:33.177 --> 00:45:34.478
Look at him.

692
00:45:36.918 --> 00:45:38.288
Put it over there.

693
00:45:42.518 --> 00:45:44.387
Thank you.

694
00:45:45.827 --> 00:45:47.597
- It's hectic, right? - It is.

695
00:45:48.398 --> 00:45:51.097
They're really salty as they've been preserved in salt.

696
00:45:51.898 --> 00:45:53.998
- They are? - Yes.

697
00:45:54.237 --> 00:45:56.498
That's why you can't season them right away.

698
00:45:56.737 --> 00:46:00.637
You have to rinse them in clean water first.

699
00:46:00.637 --> 00:46:03.777
Then put them in the basket. Do you get it?

700
00:46:04.648 --> 00:46:08.318
Rinse them in clean water...

701
00:46:09.447 --> 00:46:11.987
- and put them there? - That's right. Give it a go.

702
00:46:22.797 --> 00:46:25.228
My goodness. That's not helping.

703
00:46:25.398 --> 00:46:28.938
Wash them like how I'm washing them.

704
00:46:28.938 --> 00:46:30.467
Okay, I'll do that.

705
00:46:33.038 --> 00:46:35.108
How can a newly-wed be so weak?

706
00:46:35.108 --> 00:46:37.108
Would he be able to make a baby?

707
00:46:38.108 --> 00:46:41.617
Don't you know skinny men are better at that?

708
00:46:44.918 --> 00:46:48.858
Stop talking nonsense in front of my son-in-law.

709
00:46:49.257 --> 00:46:51.157
- That was funny. - I know.

710
00:46:51.487 --> 00:46:52.987
Skinny men are better.

711
00:47:05.237 --> 00:47:07.338
No, no. Wash them one more time.

712
00:47:08.177 --> 00:47:10.277
What... What do you mean?

713
00:47:11.047 --> 00:47:14.077
I mean you have to wash them like this again.

714
00:47:14.217 --> 00:47:16.978
Oh, like that. I see.

715
00:47:17.277 --> 00:47:19.588
- Like this. - I mean...

716
00:47:20.117 --> 00:47:21.858
wash them with much strength.

717
00:47:23.487 --> 00:47:25.088
Gosh, I can't believe this.

718
00:47:27.558 --> 00:47:28.597
Okay.

719
00:47:28.858 --> 00:47:32.427
Why on earth would you hit my son-in-law's back, you wench?

720
00:47:46.677 --> 00:47:50.047
What's this? He's really making kimchi?

721
00:47:54.188 --> 00:47:57.117
What? Why would she hit him?

722
00:47:57.688 --> 00:47:59.527
She's crazy.

723
00:48:01.327 --> 00:48:02.797
Please take my order.

724
00:48:03.558 --> 00:48:04.797
Sure!

725
00:48:08.268 --> 00:48:09.938
I'll go take it. You can leave.

726
00:48:10.338 --> 00:48:12.237
- Where to? - Where your husband is.

727
00:48:14.177 --> 00:48:16.277
If you're that concerned, you should go see him.

728
00:48:17.407 --> 00:48:19.308
But you have to come work during the weekend.

729
00:48:29.617 --> 00:48:31.858
Gosh, this is going to take forever.

730
00:48:33.358 --> 00:48:35.998
Put them over here.

731
00:48:52.277 --> 00:48:53.407
What?

732
00:48:54.577 --> 00:48:55.677
What?

733
00:49:24.007 --> 00:49:26.208
- Mr. Nam! - Yes, ma'am!

734
00:49:26.378 --> 00:49:29.077
Come carry this for me.

735
00:49:29.277 --> 00:49:30.677
Why is he just sitting there?

736
00:49:34.088 --> 00:49:35.257
How useless.

737
00:49:35.958 --> 00:49:38.188
I guess he's really here to help with kimchi.

738
00:49:38.188 --> 00:49:42.527
My gosh. He's really weird.

739
00:49:42.958 --> 00:49:44.527
Squeeze them tight.

740
00:49:49.697 --> 00:49:51.568
I've fed them.

741
00:49:53.007 --> 00:49:54.407
Where did he go though?

742
00:49:55.577 --> 00:49:58.608
Kitty. Hey, Kitty?

743
00:50:03.478 --> 00:50:04.748
Are you here?

744
00:50:09.617 --> 00:50:11.728
Are you here?

745
00:50:12.228 --> 00:50:13.927
When did you come in here?

746
00:50:17.058 --> 00:50:19.827
My gosh, you're in trouble.

747
00:50:23.498 --> 00:50:25.867
(Poem Collection)

748
00:50:25.967 --> 00:50:27.808
I've been meaning to read this.

749
00:50:29.277 --> 00:50:31.878
Would it be okay for me to borrow this?

750
00:50:34.878 --> 00:50:38.148
I'll return it after reading it.

751
00:50:48.097 --> 00:50:50.197
(To Se Hee, my love and my everything)

752
00:50:58.772 --> 00:51:00.872
(To Se Hee, my love and my everything)

753
00:51:03.608 --> 00:51:07.277
(To Se Hee, my love and my everything)

754
00:51:12.348 --> 00:51:15.647
I guess he got this from someone.

755
00:51:33.038 --> 00:51:34.837
That's enough. You can go take a rest.

756
00:51:35.007 --> 00:51:38.237
No, that's okay. I still have some more time to fill.

757
00:51:38.777 --> 00:51:41.377
Since I took my day off, I better use the most of it.

758
00:51:43.877 --> 00:51:46.118
Se Hee, are you okay?

759
00:51:46.478 --> 00:51:47.587
Of course.

760
00:51:49.018 --> 00:51:50.118
Ji Ho.

761
00:52:15.447 --> 00:52:18.118
What are you doing here? You just left last time after yelling at me.

762
00:52:22.817 --> 00:52:26.118
What's this? Is this your new business now?

763
00:52:27.217 --> 00:52:30.228
I bought the ones that are most comfortable.

764
00:52:30.288 --> 00:52:31.958
One of them must fit you.

765
00:52:32.098 --> 00:52:33.828
So try them.

766
00:52:34.598 --> 00:52:35.998
If you still find them uncomfortable,

767
00:52:36.498 --> 00:52:39.138
I'll try my best to look for...

768
00:52:40.067 --> 00:52:41.237
something that'd make you comfortable.

769
00:52:45.208 --> 00:52:46.607
I'm sorry...

770
00:52:46.607 --> 00:52:49.578
that I made you feel as though I was pressuring you.

771
00:52:49.748 --> 00:52:51.217
I'll try to fix it.

772
00:52:51.547 --> 00:52:52.848
So you should be...

773
00:52:53.848 --> 00:52:55.547
considerate of me as well.

774
00:52:58.188 --> 00:53:00.928
You know how I hate it...

775
00:53:01.127 --> 00:53:04.257
when other men look at my woman...

776
00:53:05.428 --> 00:53:07.098
and imagine weird stuff.

777
00:53:08.428 --> 00:53:10.697
Okay. I'm sorry too.

778
00:53:10.697 --> 00:53:12.138
I'm sorry for thinking it's crossing the line.

779
00:53:13.467 --> 00:53:17.067
How could you just turn off your phone? It made me anxious!

780
00:53:17.877 --> 00:53:19.678
That's because of a meeting.

781
00:53:21.107 --> 00:53:23.208
Wait for me for about an hour. Let's have dinner together.

782
00:53:24.647 --> 00:53:26.748
- Dinner? - Wait for me around here.

783
00:53:38.998 --> 00:53:40.127
Darn it.

784
00:53:40.998 --> 00:53:42.498
I'm dying for her.

785
00:53:53.978 --> 00:53:55.107
Thank you.

786
00:53:59.578 --> 00:54:00.917
Are you okay?

787
00:54:01.947 --> 00:54:05.388
How are your back and shoulders?

788
00:54:06.158 --> 00:54:09.558
They ache a bit, but I guess they'll be okay soon.

789
00:54:10.998 --> 00:54:12.127
No.

790
00:54:12.697 --> 00:54:14.728
I should go to a pharmacy...

791
00:54:14.728 --> 00:54:16.397
and get some patches before they get worse.

792
00:54:18.638 --> 00:54:19.768
Ji Ho.

793
00:54:21.038 --> 00:54:23.208
Why did you come?

794
00:54:23.607 --> 00:54:24.777
What about the cafe?

795
00:54:25.708 --> 00:54:28.107
I've arranged a few things.

796
00:54:28.107 --> 00:54:29.607
You don't have to worry about it.

797
00:54:31.717 --> 00:54:32.817
Did you...

798
00:54:34.547 --> 00:54:37.317
come because you were worried about me?

799
00:54:41.058 --> 00:54:42.158
Yes.

800
00:54:43.728 --> 00:54:44.857
I see.

801
00:54:46.627 --> 00:54:50.098
I was really happy to see you...

802
00:54:50.967 --> 00:54:52.098
here.

803
00:54:56.237 --> 00:54:57.507
Thank you.

804
00:55:08.587 --> 00:55:15.788
(Namhae Pharmacy)

805
00:55:46.158 --> 00:55:48.027
(A Visitor)

806
00:55:48.027 --> 00:55:49.688
"Meeting someone in life..."

807
00:55:51.658 --> 00:55:54.098
"is something that's actually astonishing."

808
00:55:56.098 --> 00:55:57.297
"That's because..."

809
00:55:58.138 --> 00:56:01.007
"he brings himself with his past, present,"

810
00:56:02.308 --> 00:56:03.438
"and,"

811
00:56:04.478 --> 00:56:08.248
"his future."

812
00:56:09.808 --> 00:56:13.547
"That's because someone's whole life comes along."

813
00:56:14.987 --> 00:56:16.487
"The heart is fragile."

814
00:56:17.118 --> 00:56:20.288
"Therefore, it might have been broken."

815
00:56:21.728 --> 00:56:24.458
"That heart is coming too."

816
00:56:24.458 --> 00:56:27.127
(Live your life as though nothing happened. Don't ever love someone.)

817
00:56:28.297 --> 00:56:29.967
I was curious to know...

818
00:56:32.237 --> 00:56:34.107
what kind of paths...

819
00:56:36.038 --> 00:56:37.877
your heart went through.

820
00:56:39.038 --> 00:56:43.447
(A Love Story, Christmas in August, A Moment to Remember)

821
00:56:59.058 --> 00:57:01.627
(Ji Ho's)

822
00:57:14.147 --> 00:57:17.518
The reason my heart hurts so much...

823
00:57:17.518 --> 00:57:19.547
(Don't ever love someone. You don't have the right to love.)

824
00:57:21.217 --> 00:57:24.518
when I learned of the path his heart went through...

825
00:57:25.717 --> 00:57:27.317
isn't jealousy...

826
00:57:29.788 --> 00:57:32.757
nor frustration.

827
00:57:34.527 --> 00:57:36.967
12 years ago,

828
00:57:38.067 --> 00:57:39.667
(It's Christmas Eve! Soo Ji will be a CEO, Ho Rang will be a good wife.)

829
00:57:39.667 --> 00:57:41.667
I dreamed of loving someone.

830
00:57:43.467 --> 00:57:44.578
The fact that...

831
00:57:46.678 --> 00:57:49.308
you ended your love...

832
00:57:52.647 --> 00:57:53.917
was a bit...

833
00:57:55.647 --> 00:57:56.987
sad.

834
00:57:59.518 --> 00:58:02.958
- Cheers! - Cheers!

835
00:58:08.167 --> 00:58:10.467
Gosh, my son-in-law.

836
00:58:10.467 --> 00:58:12.667
Good work today.

837
00:58:14.107 --> 00:58:15.507
Here. Let me pour you one.

838
00:58:18.277 --> 00:58:21.107
Have you ever seen anyone like him?

839
00:58:21.578 --> 00:58:24.647
My son-in-law came all the way here to help us making kimchi.

840
00:58:27.217 --> 00:58:29.487
Your daughter must be stressing him out a lot.

841
00:58:29.547 --> 00:58:31.857
You are a man. Why did you come here to help your wife's family?

842
00:58:33.058 --> 00:58:34.587
What do you mean?

843
00:58:34.987 --> 00:58:37.598
When a husband adores his wife,

844
00:58:37.598 --> 00:58:39.228
he can even kiss the fence of his wife's house.

845
00:58:39.697 --> 00:58:41.998
Don't you think he does this because my girl, Ji Ho, is beautiful?

846
00:58:41.998 --> 00:58:44.697
Stop bragging!

847
00:58:46.379 --> 00:58:47.214
Is that true?

848
00:58:47.647 --> 00:58:49.616
Did you come here because you adore your wife that much?

849
00:58:49.946 --> 00:58:51.147
Answer me!

850
00:58:52.598 --> 00:58:55.297
Stop bragging!

851
00:58:56.079 --> 00:58:56.914
Is that true?

852
00:58:57.047 --> 00:58:59.016
Did you come here because you adore your wife that much?

853
00:58:59.346 --> 00:59:00.547
Answer me!

854
00:59:00.922 --> 00:59:03.052
Yes, she is beautiful.

855
00:59:03.352 --> 00:59:05.222
That's why I'm here.

856
00:59:06.363 --> 00:59:08.193
I quite like you.

857
00:59:08.292 --> 00:59:09.992
Let me pour you a glass.

858
00:59:11.403 --> 00:59:13.003
My glass is still full.

859
00:59:13.332 --> 00:59:15.972
You should empty it now and take another one.

860
00:59:16.472 --> 00:59:17.533
I see.

861
00:59:20.803 --> 00:59:21.943
Here you are.

862
00:59:25.843 --> 00:59:26.983
Drink it.

863
00:59:29.512 --> 00:59:30.553
Drink!

864
00:59:32.253 --> 00:59:33.323
Okay.

865
00:59:35.852 --> 00:59:36.923
Drink!

866
00:59:37.963 --> 00:59:40.093
Se Hee, wait!

867
00:59:40.392 --> 00:59:42.432
- Yes? - Here!

868
00:59:42.562 --> 00:59:44.702
- Do you need me now? - Yes!

869
00:59:52.773 --> 00:59:54.642
- Let's drink now. - Let's drink!

870
00:59:55.742 --> 00:59:58.242
Are you okay? You were drinking a lot.

871
00:59:58.912 --> 01:00:00.343
I don't think...

872
01:00:03.682 --> 01:00:05.023
I'm okay.

873
01:00:05.483 --> 01:00:07.753
I think I'm almost hitting my limit.

874
01:00:07.753 --> 01:00:09.923
Where is the son-in-law?

875
01:00:09.923 --> 01:00:12.093
- Where is he? - Come with me!

876
01:00:18.832 --> 01:00:20.863
He won't let you go anywhere.

877
01:00:21.073 --> 01:00:24.173
If you keep drinking what he gives you, that can kill you.

878
01:00:25.042 --> 01:00:27.242
You should've have told me that sooner.

879
01:00:27.642 --> 01:00:30.012
Where's Ji Ho? Did she go somewhere?

880
01:00:31.542 --> 01:00:34.242
She went to get my medication, but she's not coming back yet.

881
01:00:34.452 --> 01:00:36.812
Don't come back soon then.

882
01:00:36.912 --> 01:00:38.582
Come back after walking around a bit.

883
01:00:38.783 --> 01:00:41.523
Call Ji Ho, spend some time with her and come back.

884
01:00:42.023 --> 01:00:43.923
- I will. - Let's go.

885
01:00:44.352 --> 01:00:45.762
- Are you tired? - I am.

886
01:00:45.892 --> 01:00:47.463
Let's go.

887
01:01:07.812 --> 01:01:10.113
Do you know it's actually the first time we're eating together?

888
01:01:10.452 --> 01:01:11.523
Really?

889
01:01:12.253 --> 01:01:14.222
We ate together before.

890
01:01:14.222 --> 01:01:16.492
What do you mean? We were just drinking makgeolli.

891
01:01:16.492 --> 01:01:18.662
You drank six bottles and got really drunk.

892
01:01:19.093 --> 01:01:21.062
It's made of rice anyway. So I'll count that as a meal.

893
01:01:22.892 --> 01:01:25.963
Let's eat like this from now on...

894
01:01:26.202 --> 01:01:28.803
at least three times a week. It's an order.

895
01:01:30.003 --> 01:01:31.202
But why though?

896
01:01:31.343 --> 01:01:33.542
Do you know how important it is?

897
01:01:33.542 --> 01:01:36.613
Do you have any idea why people are always talking about food?

898
01:01:37.012 --> 01:01:40.142
It's the best way to get closer to each other.

899
01:01:40.883 --> 01:01:44.053
I guess so. That's why Ji Ho fell for him too.

900
01:01:45.383 --> 01:01:47.483
What do you mean?

901
01:01:49.722 --> 01:01:51.093
I mean,

902
01:01:53.162 --> 01:01:55.533
Ji Ho fell for her landlord.

903
01:01:56.963 --> 01:01:59.602
My friend likes your friend.

904
01:02:02.033 --> 01:02:04.003
Don't tell your friend though.

905
01:02:05.202 --> 01:02:06.903
It looks like one-way love.

906
01:02:12.943 --> 01:02:14.983
Do you think it is?

907
01:02:16.852 --> 01:02:17.923
What?

908
01:02:17.923 --> 01:02:19.553
Do you think Se Hee doesn't know...

909
01:02:21.153 --> 01:02:22.622
Ji Ho likes him?

910
01:02:33.963 --> 01:02:35.003
Ji Ho.

911
01:02:37.503 --> 01:02:38.702
Ji Ho.

912
01:02:41.573 --> 01:02:43.042
Ji Ho!

913
01:03:23.852 --> 01:03:25.323
He knows Ji Ho likes him?

914
01:03:25.952 --> 01:03:27.053
Yes, he does.

915
01:03:27.553 --> 01:03:28.852
How about him then?

916
01:03:29.292 --> 01:03:31.562
How does he feel about Ji Ho?

917
01:03:37.733 --> 01:03:40.503
I like their rice. It's really fresh.

918
01:03:41.573 --> 01:03:45.343
Ji Ho has never dated anyone before. She doesn't know anything.

919
01:03:46.273 --> 01:03:47.872
I asked you because I'm worried about her.

920
01:03:55.053 --> 01:03:57.653
Se Hee must be scared because he knows.

921
01:04:01.553 --> 01:04:03.553
He knows what love is.

922
01:04:05.963 --> 01:04:08.363
That's why he's more scared. Don't you think so?

923
01:04:18.042 --> 01:04:20.042
You could have refused...

924
01:04:20.542 --> 01:04:21.713
that makgeolli.

925
01:04:22.173 --> 01:04:24.582
You are good at that normally.

926
01:04:24.983 --> 01:04:26.242
Why could you not do it today?

927
01:04:32.253 --> 01:04:34.792
- What's going on? - This is how you felt...

928
01:04:36.392 --> 01:04:38.792
when I asked you why you went to my house for the rites.

929
01:04:43.593 --> 01:04:45.832
You felt sad like I'm feeling now.

930
01:04:51.542 --> 01:04:53.073
The sea looks great.

931
01:04:54.202 --> 01:04:55.673
I haven't looked at it for a while.

932
01:04:56.713 --> 01:04:57.883
Me too.

933
01:04:58.812 --> 01:04:59.883
I mean,

934
01:05:01.682 --> 01:05:02.983
I have never looked at it...

935
01:05:06.783 --> 01:05:08.423
with someone who's not my family or my friends.

936
01:05:09.722 --> 01:05:11.762
You are neither of them.

937
01:05:14.062 --> 01:05:15.233
I've never looked at it...

938
01:05:16.693 --> 01:05:19.762
with a man.

939
01:05:24.602 --> 01:05:28.142
You haven't done a lot of things. I never expected that.

940
01:05:30.173 --> 01:05:31.343
That's true.

941
01:05:32.783 --> 01:05:36.053
I was always busy in my 20s.

942
01:05:37.582 --> 01:05:38.923
So I haven't done...

943
01:05:40.182 --> 01:05:41.892
a lot of things.

944
01:05:43.053 --> 01:05:45.262
I don't know a lot of things either.

945
01:05:47.992 --> 01:05:49.162
There's a poem...

946
01:05:50.233 --> 01:05:52.533
I liked when I was in my 20s.

947
01:05:54.403 --> 01:05:56.133
It goes like,

948
01:05:58.273 --> 01:05:59.903
"Meeting someone in life..."

949
01:06:01.003 --> 01:06:03.042
"is when someone's whole life comes along."

950
01:06:04.242 --> 01:06:05.613
"The heart is fragile."

951
01:06:06.443 --> 01:06:08.253
"Therefore, it might have been broken."

952
01:06:09.883 --> 01:06:11.582
"That heart is coming too."

953
01:06:13.483 --> 01:06:15.423
When I loved that poem,

954
01:06:16.992 --> 01:06:19.262
I didn't know what it meant.

955
01:06:20.493 --> 01:06:22.193
But when I found out the meaning,

956
01:06:24.163 --> 01:06:26.203
I couldn't like the poem anymore.

957
01:06:27.932 --> 01:06:29.233
There are a lot of things...

958
01:06:30.333 --> 01:06:33.172
you can never do again when you actually know about them.

959
01:06:36.743 --> 01:06:37.943
So I'm...

960
01:06:41.283 --> 01:06:42.953
envious of you, Ji Ho.

961
01:06:45.922 --> 01:06:47.283
You may not know about things,

962
01:06:48.752 --> 01:06:50.222
but it's a good thing.

963
01:06:53.523 --> 01:06:54.733
So...

964
01:06:55.863 --> 01:06:57.533
don't worry too much.

965
01:07:04.773 --> 01:07:06.273
It's the same to you, Se Hee.

966
01:07:08.672 --> 01:07:10.712
Even though you've seen a sea before,

967
01:07:12.012 --> 01:07:15.382
this sea you are looking at now is a different one.

968
01:07:16.913 --> 01:07:20.323
Even though you know it well, and even though you've done it before,

969
01:07:21.592 --> 01:07:25.663
Having the moment with that person is the first time for you.

970
01:07:29.663 --> 01:07:32.962
Like our marriage.

971
01:07:35.233 --> 01:07:37.273
Like the kiss at the bus stop.

972
01:07:40.602 --> 01:07:43.012
I believe what happens after those moments...

973
01:07:45.243 --> 01:07:47.882
is no one's fault.

974
01:07:49.352 --> 01:07:50.483
It...

975
01:07:51.953 --> 01:07:53.453
just happened to be that way.

976
01:07:55.793 --> 01:07:58.762
Like some waves keep on flowing...

977
01:07:59.922 --> 01:08:03.092
while the others break.

978
01:08:06.932 --> 01:08:08.873
It just happens that way.

979
01:08:09.432 --> 01:08:10.602
So...

980
01:08:12.903 --> 01:08:14.243
Se Hee,

981
01:08:15.613 --> 01:08:17.472
don't worry too much.

982
01:08:20.812 --> 01:08:22.583
It's not like...

983
01:08:24.113 --> 01:08:25.752
you know all about today...

984
01:08:27.123 --> 01:08:28.352
just because you lived yesterday.

985
01:08:30.993 --> 01:08:35.632
"Meeting someone in life is actually something astonishing."

986
01:08:38.002 --> 01:08:39.233
"That's because..."

987
01:08:40.333 --> 01:08:41.932
"someone's whole life comes along."

988
01:08:45.142 --> 01:08:46.573
"The heart is fragile."

989
01:08:48.312 --> 01:08:49.512
"Therefore,"

990
01:08:50.842 --> 01:08:52.312
"it might have been broken."

991
01:08:55.212 --> 01:08:56.382
"That heart..."

992
01:08:59.222 --> 01:09:00.422
"is coming too."

993
01:09:02.293 --> 01:09:05.422
Now I know why people go to the sea when they feel suffocated.

994
01:09:07.733 --> 01:09:11.432
You can face your heart here.

995
01:09:12.602 --> 01:09:13.703
What?

996
01:09:14.403 --> 01:09:19.172
By the way, there's something I've been wanting to correct.

997
01:09:20.972 --> 01:09:24.743
What you did at the bus stop isn't a kiss. It's more like a peck.

998
01:09:31.083 --> 01:09:32.382
Why did he have to...

999
01:09:33.653 --> 01:09:34.752
Okay.

1000
01:09:35.693 --> 01:09:37.793
In a way, it can't be called a peck either.

1001
01:09:38.193 --> 01:09:39.962
If I were to define it,

1002
01:09:40.493 --> 01:09:43.233
it'd more like lips making physical contact with other lips.

1003
01:09:43.663 --> 01:09:45.333
That should be the right definition.

1004
01:09:49.932 --> 01:09:52.602
Okay, I get it.

1005
01:09:52.972 --> 01:09:54.943
That can't be called a kiss.

1006
01:09:59.012 --> 01:10:00.812
That's not how you kiss someone.

1007
01:10:01.613 --> 01:10:04.382
Okay, I was bad at it.

1008
01:10:04.382 --> 01:10:07.823
Yes, exactly. This is...

1009
01:10:09.953 --> 01:10:11.293
how you kiss.

1010
01:10:39.983 --> 01:10:43.153
Do you get it now?

1011
01:10:45.123 --> 01:10:46.222
Or...

1012
01:10:47.493 --> 01:10:49.092
should we do it more?

1013
01:10:51.703 --> 01:10:54.373
I want to do it more.

1014
01:11:16.252 --> 01:11:17.793
His fragile heart.

1015
01:11:20.422 --> 01:11:23.363
The heart that might have been broken before.

1016
01:11:26.062 --> 01:11:27.432
His heart...

1017
01:11:32.773 --> 01:11:34.142
came to me.

1018
01:11:54.733 --> 01:11:58.432
(Because This Is My First Life)

1019
01:11:59.163 --> 01:12:02.932
I'm totally feeling the love.

1020
01:12:02.932 --> 01:12:04.903
She's pretty.

1021
01:12:04.903 --> 01:12:06.443
Don't you want to sleep with him?

1022
01:12:06.443 --> 01:12:08.543
I mean, you two live together.

1023
01:12:08.842 --> 01:12:10.573
Go wash up first.

1024
01:12:10.913 --> 01:12:12.613
Why did I do that?

1025
01:12:12.743 --> 01:12:16.153
I'm thinking about that kiss so many times a day.

1026
01:12:16.153 --> 01:12:17.682
You silly.

1027
01:12:19.283 --> 01:12:20.752
It's about our marriage.

1028
01:12:20.852 --> 01:12:23.092
Can you wait a little more?

1029
01:12:23.823 --> 01:12:26.363
I'm just curious about my girlfriend's house.

1030
01:12:26.993 --> 01:12:28.163
You're out.

1031
01:12:28.333 --> 01:12:32.102
What do young people do on a date these days?

1032
01:12:32.863 --> 01:12:34.533
I'm afraid of myself...

1033
01:12:34.972 --> 01:12:38.373
hurting someone again.

